PW is a HTTP/HTTPS daemon

 HTTPd features:
 - User-Certificate signin
 - uploads on PUT and POST with LDP-Container and retro HTML-<form> capability
 - paging containers: summarization, Link headers, sorted-ranges, offsets/cursors
 - lazy indexing via GET (fs links in a traversible container)
 - mostly conforming to http://linkeddata.github.io/SoLiD/ guidelines

 MIME-types
 - input: RDF.rb formats + Atom/RSS feeds, email, chatlogs, text-files, CSV, Markdown
 - output: RDF.rb formats + Atom/RSS, HTML (classic), HTML5+JS data-browsers

SRC git clone https://github.com/hallwaykid/pw.git ||
    git clone http://repo.or.cz/w/www.git

PRE-INSTALL any missing dependencies

# void
$ xbps-install ruby ruby-devel libgit2-devel libxml2-devel libxslt-devel source-highlight python-Pygments
$ gem install bundler

# debian
$ apt-get install ruby bundler libssl-dev libgit2-dev libxml2-dev libxslt1-dev pkg-config

INSTALL
$ cd pw/ruby
$ sh install     # symlink source to ruby $sitelibdir
$ bundle install # fetch ruby libraries

USE
$ cd ..                     # goto server-root (if elsewhere copy/link {css,js})
$ ln conf/server/Procfile . # select Rack-engine
$ foreman start             # start HTTP/HTTPS-daemons

to listen on 80/443: setcap cap_net_bind_service=+ep $(realpath `which ruby`)
              >1024: run behind apache/nginx/lighttpd (see conf for config-examples)

repl$ irb -rww

CLEAN
$ rm -rf cache index
